==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Geanticlinal
<hw>Ge`an*ti*cli"nal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ the
earth + E. <ets>anticlinal</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>An
upward bend or flexure of a considerable portion of the earth's crust,
resulting in the formation of a class of mountain elevations called
<xex>anticlinoria</xex>; -- opposed to
<xex>geosynclinal</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gear</ent>⟦br⟧
